%% Diagram: HTTP/2 over TCP — TCP-level head-of-line blocking
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant S as Server

    Note over C,S: HTTP/2 multiplexes streams onto one TCP byte stream
    S->>C: Packet 1 (Stream A)
    S->>C: Packet 2 (Stream B)
    S--xC: Packet 3 (Stream A) — LOST
    S->>C: Packet 4 (Stream C)
    S->>C: Packet 5 (Stream B)

    Note over C: TCP cannot deliver packets 4-5 to the app until #3 arrives
    Note over C: Streams B and C stall even though their bytes are buffered
